swL3MgmtMIB.name: swL3MgmtMIB
swL3MgmtMIB.description: The Structure of Layer 3 Network Management Information for the proprietary enterprise.

swL3DevCtrlRIPState.name: swL3DevCtrlRIPState
swL3DevCtrlRIPState.description: This object indicates Routing Information Protocol (RIP) version 2 function is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlOSPFState.name: swL3DevCtrlOSPFState
swL3DevCtrlOSPFState.description: This object indicates OSPF protocol is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlDVMRPState.name: swL3DevCtrlDVMRPState
swL3DevCtrlDVMRPState.description: This object indicates DVMRP protocol is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlVRRPState.name: swL3DevCtrlVRRPState
swL3DevCtrlVRRPState.description: This object indicates VRRP protocol is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlVRRPPingVirtualAddrState.name: swL3DevCtrlVRRPPingVirtualAddrState
swL3DevCtrlVRRPPingVirtualAddrState.description: This object let host can ping the virtual ip address or not. Default is disabled(2).

swL3IpCtrlTable.name: swL3IpCtrlTable
swL3IpCtrlTable.description: This table contain IP interface information.

swL3IpCtrlEntry.name: swL3IpCtrlEntry
swL3IpCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about a specific IP interface.

swL3IpCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL3IpCtrlInterfaceName
swL3IpCtrlInterfaceName.description: This object indicates the name of the IP interface.

swL3IpCtrlIfIndex.name: swL3IpCtrlIfIndex
swL3IpCtrlIfIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies the IP interface number in the swL3IpCtrlTable.

swL3IpCtrlIpAddr.name: swL3IpCtrlIpAddr
swL3IpCtrlIpAddr.description: The IP address of the interface. This object only can take the value of the unicast IP address.

swL3IpCtrlIpSubnetMask.name: swL3IpCtrlIpSubnetMask
swL3IpCtrlIpSubnetMask.description: The IP net mask for this interface.

swL3IpCtrlVlanName.name: swL3IpCtrlVlanName
swL3IpCtrlVlanName.description: This object indicates the IP control entry's VLAN name. The VLAN name in each entry must be unique in the IP Control Table.

swL3IpCtrlMode.name: swL3IpCtrlMode
swL3IpCtrlMode.description: This object indicates the IP operation mode. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. manual(2) - the IP address will be set by manual. bootp(3) - the IP address will be set automatically from BOOTP server. dhcp(4) - the IP address will be set automatically from DHCP server.

swL3IpCtrlState.name: swL3IpCtrlState
swL3IpCtrlState.description: This variable displays the status of the entry. The status used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the objects in this table.

swL3IpCtrlOperState.name: swL3IpCtrlOperState
swL3IpCtrlOperState.description: The current operational state of the IP interface.

swL3IpFdbInfoTable.name: swL3IpFdbInfoTable
swL3IpFdbInfoTable.description: A table that contains forwarding and/or filtering information. This information is used by the switch in determining how to propagate the received IP packets.

swL3IpFdbInfoEntry.name: swL3IpFdbInfoEntry
swL3IpFdbInfoEntry.description: Information about a specific IP address for which the bridge has some forwarding and/or filtering information.

swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr.name: swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr
swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr.description: A IP address for which switch has forwarding and/or filtering information.

swL3IpFdbInfoIpSubnetMask.name: swL3IpFdbInfoIpSubnetMask
swL3IpFdbInfoIpSubnetMask.description: A IP net mask for this interface.for which switch has forwarding and/or filtering information.

swL3IpFdbInfoPort.name: swL3IpFdbInfoPort
swL3IpFdbInfoPort.description: Either the value '0', or the port number of the port on which packet having a IP address equal to the value of the corresponding instance of swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr has been seen. A value of '0' indicates that the port number has not been learned but that switch does have some forwarding/filtering information about this address.

swL3IpFilterAddrMaxSupportedEntries.name: swL3IpFilterAddrMaxSupportedEntries
swL3IpFilterAddrMaxSupportedEntries.description: Maximum number of entries in the IP address filtering table (swL3IpFilterAddrCtrlTable) .

swL3IpFilterAddrCurrentTotalEntries.name: swL3IpFilterAddrCurrentTotalEntries
swL3IpFilterAddrCurrentTotalEntries.description: Current applied number of entries in the IP address filtering table. If the swL3IpFilterAddrCtrlState = dst-src-addr, then it means there are two entries in swL3IpFilterAddrCtrlTable.

swL3IpFilterAddrCtrlTable.name: swL3IpFilterAddrCtrlTable
swL3IpFilterAddrCtrlTable.description: This table defines information for the device to filter packets with specific IP address (either as the DA and/or as the SA). The IP address can be a unicast address or multicast address. This table has higher priority than both static FDB table and IGMP table. It means that if a IP address appears on this table also appears on the static FDB table, the device will use the information provide by this table to process the packet.

swL3IpFilterAddrCtrlEntry.name: swL3IpFilterAddrCtrlEntry
swL3IpFilterAddrCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about a specific unicast/multicast IP address for which the switch has filtering information.

swL3IpFilterAddrIpAddr.name: swL3IpFilterAddrIpAddr
swL3IpFilterAddrIpAddr.description: This object indicates a unicast/multicast IP address for which the switch has filtering information. But if the swL3IpFilterAddrCtrlState = src-addr, then the object can not be a multicast IP address (Class D IP address).

swL3IpFilterAddrCtrlState.name: swL3IpFilterAddrCtrlState
swL3IpFilterAddrCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. dst-addr(2) - recieved frames's destination address are currently used to be filtered as it meets with the IP address entry of the table. src-addr(3) - recieved frames's source address are currently used to be filtered as it meets with the IP address entry of the table. dst-src-addr(4) - recieved frames's destination address or source address are currently used to be filtered as it meets with the IP address entry of the table. invalid(5) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table.

swL3IpArpAgingTime.name: swL3IpArpAgingTime
swL3IpArpAgingTime.description: The timeout period in minutes for aging out dynamically learned arp information.

swL3IpStaticRouteTable.name: swL3IpStaticRouteTable
swL3IpStaticRouteTable.description: This entity's IP static Routing table.

swL3IpStaticRouteEntry.name: swL3IpStaticRouteEntry
swL3IpStaticRouteEntry.description: A particular route to a particular destination, under a particular policy.

swL3IpStaticRouteDest.name: swL3IpStaticRouteDest
swL3IpStaticRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. This object may not take a Multicast (Class D) address value. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the swL3IpStaticRouteMask object is not equal to x.

swL3IpStaticRouteMask.name: swL3IpStaticRouteMask
swL3IpStaticRouteMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the swL3IpStaticRouteDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the swL3IpStaticRouteMask by reference to the IP Address Class. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the swL3IpStaticRouteDest object is not equal to swL3IpStaticRouteDest.

swL3IpStaticRouteNextHop.name: swL3IpStaticRouteNextHop
swL3IpStaticRouteNextHop.description: On remote routes, the address of the next sys- tem en route; Otherwise, 0.0.0.0.

swL3IpStaticRouteMetric.name: swL3IpStaticRouteMetric
swL3IpStaticRouteMetric.description: The routing metric for this route.

swL3IpStaticRouteStatus.name: swL3IpStaticRouteStatus
swL3IpStaticRouteStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry is reside in the table.

swL3IpArpTable.name: swL3IpArpTable
swL3IpArpTable.description: The ARP table used for mapping from IP addresses to physical addresses.

swL3IpArpEntry.name: swL3IpArpEntry
swL3IpArpEntry.description: Each entry contains one IpAddress to `physical' address equivalence.

swL3IpArpIfIndex.name: swL3IpArpIfIndex
swL3IpArpIfIndex.description: The interface on which this entry's equivalence is effective. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

swL3IpArpNetAddress.name: swL3IpArpNetAddress
swL3IpArpNetAddress.description: The IpAddress corresponding to the media-dependent `physical' address.

swL3IpArpType.name: swL3IpArpType
swL3IpArpType.description: The type of mapping. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the swL3IpArpTable. That is, it effectively dissasociates the interface identified with said entry from the mapping identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant swL3IpArpType object.

swL3IpArpDynamicAgingTime.name: swL3IpArpDynamicAgingTime
swL3IpArpDynamicAgingTime.description: The timeout period in seconds for aging out dynamically learned arp information. If the swL3IpArpType is not dynamic(3), this object will display zero.

swL3IpArpReqRateLimitState.name: swL3IpArpReqRateLimitState
swL3IpArpReqRateLimitState.description: To enable limit ARP requests trapped to CPU or disabled.

swL3IpArpReqRateLimitValue.name: swL3IpArpReqRateLimitValue
swL3IpArpReqRateLimitValue.description: To configure how much frames per second that ARP request limit. This value will be usefull only when swL3IpArpReqRateLimitState is enabled.

swL3RelayBootpState.name: swL3RelayBootpState
swL3RelayBootpState.description: This object indicates BOOTP Relay function is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayBootpHopCount.name: swL3RelayBootpHopCount
swL3RelayBootpHopCount.description: This object indicates the maximum number of router hops that the BOOTP packets can cross.

swL3RelayBootpTimeThreshold.name: swL3RelayBootpTimeThreshold
swL3RelayBootpTimeThreshold.description: This object indicates the minimum time in seconds within which the switch must relay the BOOTP request. If this time is exceeded, the switch will drop the BOOTP packet.

swL3RelayBootpCtrlTable.name: swL3RelayBootpCtrlTable
swL3RelayBootpCtrlTable.description: This table specifys the IP address as a destination to forward (relay) BOOTP packets to.

swL3RelayBootpCtrlEntry.name: swL3RelayBootpCtrlEntry
swL3RelayBootpCtrlEntry.description: A list of information specifies the IP address as a destination to forward (relay) BOOTP packets to.

swL3RelayBootpCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL3RelayBootpCtrlInterfaceName
swL3RelayBootpCtrlInterfaceName.description: The name of the IP interface.

swL3RelayBootpCtrlState.name: swL3RelayBootpCtrlState
swL3RelayBootpCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry is reside in the table.

swL3RelayDnsState.name: swL3RelayDnsState
swL3RelayDnsState.description: This object indicates DNS Relay function is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayDnsPrimaryServer.name: swL3RelayDnsPrimaryServer
swL3RelayDnsPrimaryServer.description: This object indicates the address of the primary DNS server.

swL3RelayDnsSecondaryServer.name: swL3RelayDnsSecondaryServer
swL3RelayDnsSecondaryServer.description: This object indicates the address of the secondary DNS server.

swL3RelayDnsCacheState.name: swL3RelayDnsCacheState
swL3RelayDnsCacheState.description: This object indicates DNS Relay cache is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayDnsStaticTableState.name: swL3RelayDnsStaticTableState
swL3RelayDnsStaticTableState.description: This object indicates DNS Relay static table is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlTable.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlTable
swL3RelayDnsCtrlTable.description: This table display the current DNS relay static table.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlEntry.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlEntry
swL3RelayDnsCtrlEntry.description: A list of information display the current DNS relay static table.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlDomainName.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlDomainName
swL3RelayDnsCtrlDomainName.description: The domain name of the entry.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlIpAddr.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlIpAddr
swL3RelayDnsCtrlIpAddr.description: The IP address of the entry.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlState.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlState
swL3RelayDnsCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry is reside in the table.

swL3Md5Table.name: swL3Md5Table
swL3Md5Table.description: This table display the current MD5 key table.

swL3Md5Entry.name: swL3Md5Entry
swL3Md5Entry.description: A list of information display the current MD5 key table.

swL3Md5Key.name: swL3Md5Key
swL3Md5Key.description: An MD5 password of up to 16 bytes.

swL3Md5State.name: swL3Md5State
swL3Md5State.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry is reside in the table.

swL3RouteRedistriTable.name: swL3RouteRedistriTable
swL3RouteRedistriTable.description: Route redistribution allows routers on the network. That are running different routing protocols to exchange routing information. This is accomplished by comparing the routes stored in the vairous routers routing tables and assinging appropriate metrics. This information is then exchanged among the various routers according to the individual routers current routing protocol.

swL3RouteRedistriEntry.name: swL3RouteRedistriEntry
swL3RouteRedistriEntry.description: A list of information display the route redistribution table.

swL3RouteRedistriSrcProtocol.name: swL3RouteRedistriSrcProtocol
swL3RouteRedistriSrcProtocol.description: Allows the selection of the protocol of the source device.

swL3RouteRedistriDstProtocol.name: swL3RouteRedistriDstProtocol
swL3RouteRedistriDstProtocol.description: Allows the selection of the protocol of the destination device.

swL3RouteRedistriType.name: swL3RouteRedistriType
swL3RouteRedistriType.description: Allows the selection of one of the methods for calcalculating the metric value.

swL3RouteRedistriMetric.name: swL3RouteRedistriMetric
swL3RouteRedistriMetric.description: Allows the entry of an OSPF interface cost. This is analogous to a Hop Count in the RIP routing protocol. The value '0' indicates default value.

swL3RouteRedistriState.name: swL3RouteRedistriState
swL3RouteRedistriState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry is reside in the table.

swL3OspfHostTable.name: swL3OspfHostTable
swL3OspfHostTable.description: The list of Hosts, and their metrics, that the router will advertise as host routes.

swL3OspfHostEntry.name: swL3OspfHostEntry
swL3OspfHostEntry.description: A metric to be advertised, for a given type of service, when a given host is reachable.

swL3OspfHostIpAddress.name: swL3OspfHostIpAddress
swL3OspfHostIpAddress.description: The IP Address of the Host.

swL3OspfHostTOS.name: swL3OspfHostTOS
swL3OspfHostTOS.description: The Type of Service of the route being configured.

swL3OspfHostStatus.name: swL3OspfHostStatus
swL3OspfHostStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the entry. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

swL3OspfHostAreaID.name: swL3OspfHostAreaID
swL3OspfHostAreaID.description: The Area the Host Entry is to be found within. By default, the area that a subsuming OSPF interface is in, or 0.0.0.0

swL3VrrpOperTable.name: swL3VrrpOperTable
swL3VrrpOperTable.description: Operations table for a VRRP router which consists of a sequence (i.e., one or more conceptual rows) of 'swL3VrrpOperEntry' items.

swL3VrrpOperEntry.name: swL3VrrpOperEntry
swL3VrrpOperEntry.description: An entry in the swL3VrrpOperTable containing the operational characteristics of a virtual router. On a VRRP router, a given virtual router is identified by a combination of the IF index and VRID.

swL3VrrpOperVrId.name: swL3VrrpOperVrId
swL3VrrpOperVrId.description: This object contains the Virtual Router Identifier (VRID).

swL3VrrpOperCriticalIpAddr.name: swL3VrrpOperCriticalIpAddr
swL3VrrpOperCriticalIpAddr.description: To make sure the ip interface connected by this virtual router is alive or not.

swL3VrrpOperCriticalIpState.name: swL3VrrpOperCriticalIpState
swL3VrrpOperCriticalIpState.description: To enable or disable the feature of critical IP.

swL3VrrpOperHoldDownTimer.name: swL3VrrpOperHoldDownTimer
swL3VrrpOperHoldDownTimer.description: When VRRP is started, it need to spend this period of time to let the routing would be leared as well. The unit of this object is second.

swL3RoutePrefEntry.name: swL3RoutePrefEntry
swL3RoutePrefEntry.description: An entry of Ip Route Pref Table.

swL3RoutePrefValue.name: swL3RoutePrefValue
swL3RoutePrefValue.description: This value is a preference value for the given protocol.

swL3DvmrpInterfaceTable.name: swL3DvmrpInterfaceTable
swL3DvmrpInterfaceTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the router's multicast- capable interfaces.

swL3DvmrpInterfaceEntry.name: swL3DvmrpInterfaceEntry
swL3DvmrpInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the swL3DvmrpInterfaceTable.

swL3DvmrpInterfaceIfIndex.name: swL3DvmrpInterfaceIfIndex
swL3DvmrpInterfaceIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which DVMRP is enabled.

swL3DvmrpInterfaceNeighborTimeout.name: swL3DvmrpInterfaceNeighborTimeout
swL3DvmrpInterfaceNeighborTimeout.description: The time period for DVMRP will hold Neithbor Router reports before issuing poison route messages. The unit is second.

swL3DvmrpInterfaceProbe.name: swL3DvmrpInterfaceProbe
swL3DvmrpInterfaceProbe.description: DVMRP defines an extension to IGMP that allows routers to query other routers to determine if a multicast group is present on an given router subnetwork or not. This is referred to as a 'probe'. The unit is second.
